\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2650350 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13519019\charrsid2650350 
Chocolate. Well, Cadbury's milk tray chocolates came out I think perhaps I would be fourteen you see and was two shillings a pound, sixpence a quarter. If you were very wealthy you'd have a quarter each. But if w
e weren't wealthy we'd pool our res - we were very good at - if I had so much and Lily had so much we'd always pool it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14045772\charrsid2650350 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13519019\charrsid2650350 As an only child you were willing to share?
