r own shops in those days and there was a sprinkling of solicitors but mostly they were - the - the sons, you see, the boys I knew - my parents boys - nearly all went in for professions. It was more money. And - a lot of the boys I knew were solicitors an
d - and accountants. That sort of thing. They weren't tradesmen in the sense like my father and my grandfather were.
