Oh, I just applied. Saw it advertised in the Echo and applied and I went and had and interview and he asked me could I do decimals and I said yes. And he said, oh do yo
u mean it. So I said yes, yes, I can do decimals - I could do plain sums. And he - he was no good for a man for interviewing you at all because he didn't know anything at all - only thing he knew well if you could do decimals well you must be all right.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14045772\charrsid2650350 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13519019\charrsid2650350 What did you get paid at that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2650350 AT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13519019\charrsid2650350 
A pound a week. And - you got holidays - with pay - I - November I started - I know my father's boat was sunk just about the time I started - May. And then I got a weeks holiday in - August - then end of August y
ou see. As pe - oh and I got a fortnight in - September - that first year. Yes. Very good. And then you got a bonus - got a bonus of three pounds at the end - at June - the end of the half year.
\par 
